Ecological notes : common in broad-leaved and carr woodland; also found in mixed woodland; wet and humid heathland; wetlands including fen; reed and sedge beds,
Sphagnum
kettlehole, raised mire and water meadows; gravel pits; old hedges; grassland with pingo pools; unimproved calcareous grassland; parkland; gardens; grounds of horticultural research station; school grounds with old poplars; decaying vegetation by race track ; vegetable detritus on cliff top with salty spray; shingle beach; greenhouses; mushroom farms. Reared from nests of dormouse, mole, moorhen, coot, linnet and blackbird; rotten fungus-covered wood; daffodil bulbs; haystack; old wasp nest; rotting onions; stable manure; mushroom compost; the fungi
Laetiporus sulphureus
and
Lepiota cristata
; soil from rabbit burrow; crowns of sea kale. i–xii.
